cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with ship detection using high-resolution remote sensing images, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new representation method for ships' orientation, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The dataset also involves geographical information, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
